<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="AI2" checkit-title="Arc Length">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider the curve <m>y=\sqrt{5 \, x + 3}</m> defined on <m>[1, 3]</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Estimate the arclength of this curve with <m>5</m> line segments with <m>\Delta x = 0.4</m>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Find an integral that computes the arclength of this curve.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <me>
               \begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|}
              \hline
              x_i
              &amp;
              x_{i+1}
              &amp;
              f(x_{i})
              &amp;
              f(x_{i+1})
              &amp;
              \text{Length of segment}          
              \\
              \hline
               1
              &amp; 
               1.4
              &amp;
               2.8284
              &amp; 
               3.1623
              &amp;
               0.521         
                  \\
               1.4
              &amp; 
               1.7999999999999998
              &amp;
               3.1623
              &amp; 
               3.4641
              &amp;
               0.5011         
                  \\
               1.8
              &amp; 
               2.2
              &amp;
               3.4641
              &amp; 
               3.7417
              &amp;
               0.4869         
                  \\
               2.2
              &amp; 
               2.6
              &amp;
               3.7417
              &amp; 
               4.0
              &amp;
               0.4762         
                  \\
               2.6
              &amp; 
               3.0
              &amp;
               4.0
              &amp; 
               4.2426
              &amp;
               0.4678         
                  \\
              
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
              The estimated length of this curve is 2.453.      
                </li>
                <li>
                    The arclength is computed via <me>\int_{ 1 }^{ 3 }\sqrt{1+ \left(\frac{5}{2 \, \sqrt{5 \, x + 3}}\right)^2}dx.</me> 
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
